\v 2 And that we may be delivered from unreasonable and wicked men; for not all have faith.
\p
\v 3 But the Lord is faithful, who shall establish you, and keep \add you\add* from the evil one.
\p
\v 4 And we have confidence in the Lord touching you, that ye both do, and will do, the things which we command you.
\p
\v 5 And the Lord direct your hearts into the love of God, and into the patience of Christ.
\p
\v 6 ¶ Now we command you, brethren, in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ, that ye withdraw yourselves from every brother that walketh disorderly, and not according to the truth which ye received of us.
\p
\v 7 For yourselves know how ye ought to follow us; because we behaved not ourselves disorderly among you;
\p
\v 8 Neither did we eat any man’s bread for nothings but wrought with labour and travail night and day, that we might not be chargeable to any of you;
\p
\v 9 Not because we have not the right, but to make ourselves an example unto you, that ye should follow us.
\p
\v 10 For even when we were with you, this we commanded you, that if any would not work, neither should he eat.
\p
\v 11 For we hear that there are some who walk among you, disorderly, working not at all, but are busy-bodies.
\p
\v 12 Now them that are such we command and exhort by our Lord Jesus Christ, that with quietness they work, and eat their own bread.
\p
\v 13 But ye, brethren, be not weary in well doing.
